### Section 1 — Ethical Conditions

The Licensed Rights are expressly conditioned on the Licensee's ongoing
compliance with the following. The Licensee SHALL NOT, whether directly or
indirectly through agents or assigns:

**1.1.** Infringe upon any person's right to life or security of person, engage
in extrajudicial killings, or commit murder (See Article 3, UN Universal
Declaration of Human Rights; Article 6, ICCPR).

**1.2.** Hold any person in slavery, servitude, or forced labor; or contribute
to the institutions of slavery, slave trading, or unlawful child labor
(See Article 4, UDHR; Article 8, ICCPR).

**1.3.** Torture or subject any person to cruel, inhumane, or degrading
treatment or punishment (See Article 5, UDHR; Article 7, ICCPR).

**1.4.** Discriminate on the basis of sex, gender, sexual orientation, race,
ethnicity, nationality, religion, caste, age, or disability (See Article 7,
UDHR; Article 26, ICCPR).

**1.5.** Deploy this software as a component of any mass surveillance system,
including systems that track, profile, or monitor individuals without their
free, prior, and informed consent.

**1.6.** Deploy this software as a component of any military weapons system,
autonomous weapons platform, or lethal targeting system.

**1.7.** Prevent Workers from freely organizing, forming unions, or engaging in
collective bargaining (See Article 20, UDHR; ILO Convention No. 87).

**1.8.** Commit ecocide, defined as acts with a substantial likelihood of
causing severe and either widespread or long-term damage to the environment,
including:

- **(a)** irreversible harm to ecosystems, biodiversity, watersheds, or
  atmosphere;
- **(b)** nationally or globally significant increases in carbon emissions
  resulting from the Licensee's products or infrastructure, including data
  centers operated in service of AI systems that incorporate this software.

**1.9.** Arbitrarily deprive any person of property, subject any person to
arbitrary arrest or detention, or engage in arbitrary interference with a
person's privacy or correspondence (See Articles 9, 12, 17, UDHR).

**1.10.** Forcibly remove indigenous peoples from their lands or territories,
or dispossess indigenous peoples of their intellectual property or traditional
knowledge without free, prior, and informed consent (See Articles 8 and 10,
UN Declaration on the Rights of Indigenous Peoples).

The Licensee SHALL:

**1.11.** Provide equal pay for equal work without discrimination on the basis
of sex, gender, race, ethnicity, nationality, religion, caste, age, or
disability, except where differentials are based on seniority, merit, or
quantity/quality of production (See 29 U.S.C.A. § 206(d)(1); Article 23,
UDHR; Article 7, ICESCR).

**1.12.** Allow reasonable limitation of working hours and periodic paid
holidays (See Article 24, UDHR; Article 7, ICESCR).

**1.13.** Make supply chain data publicly accessible, including manufacturers,
top-tier suppliers, subcontractors, and component producers, on a website
accessible via common internet search.

